The Minister of State for Finance, Budget and National Planning, Mr Clement Agba has said the Federal Executive Council (FEC) has approved the request for a 500millionn Euros Sovereign Guarantee for the Bank of Industry, to support industrialization, micro-small and medium value chain in Nigeria and to facilitate the creation of new jobs.  Briefing State House Correspondent at the end of FEC meeting presided over by President Muhammadu at the Presidential Villa, Abuja, he said the facility, which is at single-digit, will be sourced through the Ministry of Finance adding that the loan will be swapped in naira for easy access.  The Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami, also disclosed that the council approved a Justice Sector Policy for the country essentially to reform the sector by simplifying access to justice.  The policy, he said, would ensure the speedy determination of justice, quality of justice and access to justice adding that the council also approved a memo seeking to repeal the Geneva Convention and re-enact it to accord greater access to justice by prisoners of war.  Our State House Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the Minister of Power, Saleh Mamman, said FEC also approved the memo for the release of two million dollars as counterpart fund for the West African Power Pole (WAPP).